(4, 'So how does it work?', '[HTML]\r\n<!-- click on the icon with the eye (second one) on the upper right to see how this page looks like! -->\r\n\r\n<h3>__ELEMENTTITLE__</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Hello __FORENAME__ __NAME__</b> (__USERNAME__), this lab is just for getting familiar with the lab system!\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nYou find all elements you''ll find in a &quot;real&quot; lab here to get familar with them.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIn a &quot;real&quot; prelab you will find many information that will help you (and is necessary) during the lab.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All labs have two parts:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The prelab</li>\r\n<li>The lab</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe <b>prelab</b> should give you the <b>theoretical background</b> of what you will do later on in the lab session. The more careful you read the texts, the easier the lab will be for you.<br />\r\nThere are multiple choice questions after most of the prelab sections. These questions should help you to recover and memorize the most important aspects of the topics you have just read about.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nYou won''t have to wait until someone corrects your multiple choice questions. On the page with all prelab questions (last menu entry of the prelab) you find a button "<b>check prelab</b>". Clicking it makes the system check your answers. You''ll see immediately what was wrong and what was right and sometimes you will also get some information why that is the answer.<br />\r\nYou have multiple attempts to answer the questions. By default you have three (3) attempts (that value can be changed in the config file).\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To be able to perform the lab, <b>each groupmember</b> has to have answered <b>all prelab-questions</b>. When all your teammates are finished with the prelab session, the lab session will become visible to you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the <b>lab</b> you will use the techniques you read about in the prelab. You solve some exercises together as a team. The available lab text gives you some instructions. During the lab you''ll  have to <b>answer some questions</b>. You do this as a team (as you will see all of you have the same answer fields). You should switch formulating the answers so that each groupmember writes down some of the answers. It is also a challenge to formulate one''s thoughts clearly...</p>', '', 1, 1, '2006-03-11 19:10:58: Marc-Oliver Pahl'),
(5, 'You logged in...', '[HTML]\r\n<!-- click on the icon with the eye (second one) on the upper right to see how this page looks like! -->\r\n\r\n<h3>__ELEMENTTITLE__</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Hello __FORENAME__ __NAME__</b> (__USERNAME__), congratulations you are logged in right now!\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div align="center">\r\n <img src="../pix/logged_in_400_84.jpg" border="0" alt="Elevator control panel in Uppsala, Sweden; &copy; Marc-Oliver Pahl Spring 2003" />\r\n <div style="padding-left: 0.5em; padding-right: 0.5em; text-align: center; font-size: 0.7em;">Elevator control panel in Uppsala, Sweden; &copy; Marc-Oliver Pahl Spring 2003</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>To get startet...</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>You can come back to this page by clicking on <b>First steps</b> in the menu on the left.</li>\r\n\r\n <li><b>Act as user:</b> If you did not use the system before I would suggest to <b>perform</b> the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=l2&__LINKQUERY__"><b>demonstration lab</b></a> to see what basic functionality is available to the users. After having explored and filled the answers <b>close the lab</b>!</li>\r\n\r\n <li>To test the other roles you can have (mainly corrector, editor), you have to give yourself some rights first. Go to the go to the <a href="../pages/manageUsers.php?__LINKQUERY__">user properties</a> page and check all boxes to give you all rights and <b>save</b>.</li>\r\n \r\n <li>Next go to the <a href="../pages/myRights.php?__LINKQUERY__">my rights</a> page and check the boxes there to apply your rights change (alternatively you can log out and in again).<br>\r\n     You can use the <a href="../pages/myRights.php?__LINKQUERY__">my rights</a> page later to restrict your role temporarily as roles mean appearing control elements and you might get rid of them when you want to correct but not to edit for instance.</li>\r\n\r\n <li><b>Act as corrector:</b> Next I propose to take a <b>corrector</b>''s role. The corrector takes advantage of the example solution viewing right and the corrector state. View the demonstration lab again from the <b>correctors point of view</b> by just opening it again. The different role is reflected in a different view.<br>\r\nYou should start at the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=l2.labStatus&__LINKQUERY__">lab status</a> and click on your name there since you will see your data then...<br />\r\nYou''ll see that you can give credits and comments on the solutions as well as have a look at the prelab results.<br />\r\nWhile not having corrected all inputs go to the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=l2.labStatus&__LINKQUERY__">lab status</a> and press &quot;update&quot;. The system will indicate you which inputs are corrected yet. After all inputs are corrected these indicators will disappear and the icon on the right will turn green...</li>\r\n\r\n <li><b>Act as editor:</b> As next step <b>for an editor</b> I would suggest to go to the <a href="../pages/myRights.php?__LINKQUERY__">my rights</a> page and give you back the content editor right (you might remove the correctors rights). Now view the demonstration lab again from the <b>editors point of view</b>. You''ll see that you have some more icons that give you editing functionality.<br />\r\nA good starting point to get familar with the editing is the tutorial <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p6&__LINKQUERY__">&quot;How the demonstration lab was created...&quot;</a>.</li>\r\n\r\n <li>Now you are already familiar with the basics of the system... <b>Enjoy the system!</b></li>\r\n</ul>', 'First steps', 1, 0, '2010-01-19 19:59:51: Marc-Oliver Pahl'),
(6, 'How was the demonstration lab created?', '[HTML]\r\n<!-- click on the icon with the eye (second one) on the upper right to see how this page looks like! -->\r\n\r\n<h3>__ELEMENTTITLE__</h3>\r\n\r\n<div class="inNotice">This brief tutorial should give you a short overview of the system''s authoring process...</div>\r\n<div class="inNotice">To perform the tutorial you must be a content editor!</div>\r\n<div class="inNotice">You might want to open this tutorial again in another tab or window to be able to read and explore, so just click <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p6&nomenu=true&__LINKQUERY__" target="_blank">here</a>.</div>\r\n\r\n<ol><li><!-- topic 1 -->\r\n The Prelab content:\r\n\r\n  <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <ul>\r\n  <!-- page element -->\r\n   <li><div style="width: 40px; display: inline; float: right;"><img src="../syspix/button_new_39x36.gif" border="0" /></div>\r\n   Creating the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p4&__LINKQUERY__">prelab''s text element</a>:\r\n    <ul>\r\n     <li>Click on <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p2&__LINKQUERY__">elements</a> in the menu.</li>\r\n     <li>Create a <a href="../pages/edit.php?address=p1&saveAsNew&__LINKQUERY__">new page element</a> and insert all information as you need it.</li>\r\n     <li>Save the element and <b>note down the address</b> the system tells you the element was saved as since you need it later to plug the elements together. (In my case it was p4).</li>\r\n     <div class="inNotice">Take care of the visibility rights!<br />\r\n     In my case the element should <b>only be visible inside a collection</b> and <b>only to users that are logged in</b> so that the page can only be viewed inside our demonstration lab.</div>\r\n    </ul>\r\n   </li>\r\n\r\n  <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <!-- multiple choice element -->\r\n   <li><div style="width: 40px; display: inline; float: right;"><img src="../syspix/button_new_multichoice_39x36.gif" border="0" /></div>\r\n   Creating the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=m2&__LINKQUERY__">prelab''s multiple choice element</a>:\r\n    <ul>\r\n     <li>Click on <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p2&__LINKQUERY__">elements</a> in the menu.</li>\r\n     <li>Create a <a href="../pages/edit.php?address=m1&saveAsNew&__LINKQUERY__">new multiple choice element</a> and insert all information as you need it.\r\n      <div class="inNotice">The system will toss the answers for each user before presenting them to him so don''t worry if you put your right answers always on top in editing mode...</div>\r\n     </li>\r\n     <li>Save the element and <b>note down the address</b> the system tells you the element was saved as since you need it later to plug the elements together. (In my case it was m2).</li>\r\n     <div class="inNotice">Take care of the visibility rights!<br />\r\n     In my case the element should <b>only be visible inside a collection</b> and <b>only to users that are logged in</b> so that the page can only be viewed inside our demonstration lab.</div>\r\n    </ul>\r\n   </li>\r\n\r\n  <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <!-- collection element -->\r\n   <li><div style="width: 40px; display: inline; float: right;"><img src="../syspix/button_new_collection_39x36.gif" border="0" /></div>\r\n   After having created the single elements of the prelab we can aggregate them right now inside the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=c2&__LINKQUERY__">prelab''s collection</a>:\r\n    <ul>\r\n     <li>Click on <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p2&__LINKQUERY__">elements</a> in the menu.</li>\r\n     <li>Create a <a href="../pages/edit.php?address=c1&saveAsNew&__LINKQUERY__">new collection</a>.\r\n      <ul>\r\n       <li>The content of the new collection will be our two elements from above. In my case I entered p4 [return] m2.</li>\r\n      </ul>\r\n     </li>\r\n     <li>Save the element and <b>note down the address</b> the system tells you the element was saved as since you need it later to plug the elements together. (In my case it was c2).</li>\r\n     <div class="inNotice">Here we have a little different visibility rights!<br />\r\n     The single elements will be presented to the users specified with the element.<br />\r\n     Since we told them only to be visible inside a collection they will only be visible as part of this collection (not standalone).<br />\r\n     Since I want this collection only to be visible in my demonstration lab I tell it so (visible <b>only inside a collection</b>) and <br/>\r\n     leave the <b>schedule options unchecked</b> (You can do some advanced stuff with them like presenting some of the content earlier...).</div>\r\n    </ul>\r\n   </li>\r\n\r\n  <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <!-- prelab done -->\r\n   <li>So we are <b>done</b> with the <b>prelab</b> content yet!</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n </li><!-- /topic 1 -->\r\n\r\n\r\n<li><!-- topic 2 -->\r\n<!-- the lab content -->\r\n The Lab content:\r\n\r\n  <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <div class="inNotice">The same steps as above only the m(ultiple choice) element gets an i(nput) element...</div>\r\n  <ul>\r\n\r\n  <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <!-- page element -->\r\n   <li><div style="width: 40px; display: inline; float: right;"><img src="../syspix/button_new_39x36.gif" border="0" /></div>\r\n   Create the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p7&__LINKQUERY__">lab''s text element</a> and save it.<br />\r\n   Don''t forget to <b>note down the address</b> the system tells you the element was saved as since you need it later to plug the elements together. (In my case it was p7).</li>\r\n\r\n  <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <!-- input element -->\r\n   <li><div style="width: 40px; display: inline; float: right;"><img src="../syspix/button_new_input_39x36.gif" border="0" /></div>\r\n   Creating the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=m2&__LINKQUERY__">lab''s input element</a>:\r\n    <ul>\r\n     <li>Click on <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p2&__LINKQUERY__">elements</a> in the menu.</li>\r\n     <li>Create a <a href="../pages/edit.php?address=i1&saveAsNew&__LINKQUERY__">new input element</a> and insert all information as you need it.</li>\r\n     <li>Save the element and <b>note down the address</b> the system tells you the element was saved as since you need it later to plug the elements together. (In my case it was i2).</li>\r\n     <div class="inNotice">Take care of the visibility rights!<br />\r\n     In my case the element should <b>only be visible inside a collection</b> and <b>only to users that are logged in</b> so that the page can only be viewed inside our demonstration lab.</div>\r\n    </ul>\r\n   </li>\r\n\r\n  <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <!-- collection element -->\r\n   <li><div style="width: 40px; display: inline; float: right;"><img src="../syspix/button_new_collection_39x36.gif" border="0" /></div>\r\n   Now we will aggregate the single lab elements inside the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=c3&__LINKQUERY__">lab''s collection</a>:\r\n    <ul>\r\n     <li>Click on <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p2&__LINKQUERY__">elements</a> in the menu.</li>\r\n     <li>Create a <a href="../pages/edit.php?address=c1&saveAsNew&__LINKQUERY__">new collection</a>.\r\n      <ul>\r\n       <li>The content of the new collection will be our two elements from above. In my case I entered p7 [return] i2.</li>\r\n      </ul>\r\n     </li>\r\n     <li>Save the element and <b>note down the address</b> the system tells you the element was saved as since you need it later to plug the elements together. (In my case it was c3).</li>\r\n     <div class="inNotice">Here we have a little different visibility rights!<br />\r\n     The single elements will be presented to the users specified with the element.<br />\r\n     Since we told them only to be visible inside a collection they will only be visible as part of this collection (not standalone).<br />\r\n     Since I want this collection only to be visible in my demonstration lab I tell it so (visible <b>only inside a collection</b>) and <br/>\r\n     leave the <b>schedule options unchecked</b> (You can do some advanced stuff with them like presenting some of the content earlier...).</div>\r\n    </ul>\r\n   </li>\r\n\r\n   <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <!-- lab content done -->\r\n   <li>So we are <b>done</b> with the <b>lab content</b> too!</li>\r\n   <li><div class="inNotice">If you have a look at the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=C5&__LINKQUERY__">lab content</a> you will see that I added some more stuff... Since the authoring process is the same as described above I will only point out one more thing: <b>The aggregation of collections</b>.<br />\r\n   I aggregate <a href="../pages/view.php?address=c3&__LINKQUERY__">c3</a> and <a href="../pages/view.php?address=c4&__LINKQUERY__">c4</a> in <a href="../pages/view.php?address=C5&__LINKQUERY__"><b>C</b>5</a>.<br />\r\n   As you see there also exists a big C. So what is the difference? Well open the little c: <a href="../pages/view.php?address=c5&__LINKQUERY__"><b>c</b>5</a> and then the big one: <a href="../pages/view.php?address=C5&__LINKQUERY__"><b>C</b>5</a>.<br />\r\n   As you can see the <b>little c</b> shows <b>all</b> aggregated elements togehter <b>on one page</b>. The <b>big</b> one splits <b>each</b> aggregated element on a <b>separate page</b>.</div>\r\n   </li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n </li><!-- /topic 2 -->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li><!-- topic 3 -->\r\n <!-- The lab -->\r\n Finally the two content parts have to be aggregated into <a href="../pages/view.php?address=l2&__LINKQUERY__">the demonstration lab</a>:\r\n\r\n  <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <ul>\r\n\r\n  <!-- lab element -->\r\n   <li><div style="width: 40px; display: inline; float: right;"><img src="../syspix/button_new_lab_39x36.gif" border="0" /></div>\r\n   Creating the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=l2&__LINKQUERY__">lab element</a>:\r\n    <ul>\r\n     <li>Click on <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p2&__LINKQUERY__">elements</a> in the menu.</li>\r\n     <li>Create a <a href="../pages/edit.php?address=l1&saveAsNew&__LINKQUERY__">new lab</a>.</li>\r\n     <li>Choose your prelab collection (in our case c6=c2+suggestions/ complaints) and your lab collection (c5).\r\n     <div class="inNotice">\r\n      Here we set different visibility rights.\r\n      <ul>\r\n       <li>The lab might be visible even outside a collection.</li>\r\n       <li>The visibility should depend on a schedule (visible during and after).</li>\r\n      </ul>\r\n     </div>\r\n     </li>\r\n     <li>Save the element and <b>note down the address</b> the system tells you the element was saved. This is the address you can open the lab with. (In my case it was l2).</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n   </li>\r\n\r\n  </ul>\r\n </li><!-- /topic 3 -->\r\n\r\n\r\n<li><!-- topic 4 -->\r\n So we are <b>done</b>.\r\n\r\n <hr size="1" />\r\n\r\n  <div class="inNotice">You might want to <b>integrate the new lab into the menu</b>. So click on <a href="../pages/editMenu.php?__LINKQUERY__">edit menu</a> and look how I did it with the demonstration lab.<br />\r\n  I just added <span class="code">shortcut0 = &quot;!l2&quot;</span>. So can you do with your new lab. Just add <span class="code">shortcut[nextIndex] = &quot;!l[yourIndex]&quot;</span>...</div>\r\n\r\n  <div class="inNotice">You might also want to <b>make a schedule</b> for the new lab. To do this you have to be allowed to make schedules!<br />\r\n  Got to the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=s1&__LINKQUERY__">schedule page</a> and click on the icon on the top right to <a href="../pages/edit.php?address=s1&saveAsNew&__LINKQUERY__">create a new schedule</a>. Choose your lab, set the date and save. That''s it...</div>\r\n\r\n  <div class="inNotice">\r\n  You can also define and use <b>custom styles</b> by <a href="../pages/editUsrCss.php?__LINKQUERY__">editing the stylesheet</a>...\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n </li><!-- /topic 4 -->\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="inNotice">The icons at each element might allow you to perform aboves actions more quickly. Just try it out.<br />\r\nDon''t worry, before deleting something you will get warned...<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style="list-style-image: url(''../syspix/button_link2_13x12.gif'');">Shortcut to this element (to copy and paste into a page like this) with added __LINKQUERY&#95;&#95; tag.</li>\r\n\r\n <li style="list-style-image: url(''../syspix/button_edit_13x12.gif'');">Edit this element.</li>\r\n\r\n <li style="list-style-image: url(''../syspix/button_view_13x12.gif'');">View this element.</li>\r\n\r\n <li style="list-style-image: url(''../syspix/button_new_13x12.gif'');">Create a new element of this element''s type.</li>\r\n\r\n <li style="list-style-image: url(''../syspix/button_delete_13x12.gif'');">Delete this element.</li>\r\n\r\n <li style="list-style-image: url(''../syspix/button_manage_elements_13x12.gif'');">Same as &quot;elements&quot; from the menu (Managing the elements).</li>\r\n\r\n <li style="list-style-image: url(''../syspix/button_history_13x12.gif'');">This element''s history (in case of an answerable element (m/ i) you will have two of these icons. One will be the history of the user answers and one of the element.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="inNotice">\r\n  At the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p2&__LINKQUERY__">Managing the elements page</a> we only used the links left of the image but there are also some on the right. if you click on them you get a list of all existing elements of this type...\r\n</div>', '', 0, 0, '2006-03-11 19:10:58: Marc-Oliver Pahl'),
(7, 'In the lab...', '[HTML]\r\n<!-- click on the icon with the eye (second one) on the upper right to see how this page looks like! -->\r\n\r\n<!-- <h3>__ELEMENTTITLE__</h3> -->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Well done __FORENAME__ __NAME__</b>, you and alll your teammates finished the prelab!\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNow you have access to this lab part. Here you will find the exercises.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<b>You can answer</b> the questions <b>during the <a href="../pages/view.php?address=s1&__LINKQUERY__">schedule</a></b>. If the schedule is up the answers will close automatically.<br />\r\nIf <b>you finish the lab earlier</b> than the schedule end is set <b>you should close</b> the lab to enable the correctors to correct your answers earlier...<br />\r\nHow to do this? Just as with the prelab: Click on all lab questions in the menu and press the close lab button on top.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSo in a real lab here would be some instructions on how to perform a cool experiment...\r\n</p>', '', 0, 1, '2006-03-11 19:10:58: Marc-Oliver Pahl'),
(8, 'Button pictogramm explanation', '[HTML]\r\n<!-- click on the icon with the eye (second one) on the upper right to see how this page looks like! -->\r\n\r\n<div class="inNotice">\r\n<img src="../syspix/button_previous_13x12.gif" border="0" /> <img src="../syspix/button_next_13x12.gif" border="0" /> If you have multiple pages you can navigate with the arrows. The <img src="../syspix/button_toc_13x12.gif" border="0" /> links to the table of content.</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="inNotice">\r\n<img src="../syspix/button_history_13x12.gif" border="0" /> For each element there exists a <b>history</b>.<br />\r\nFor instance you can see who edited the answer above by clicking on the lower book. Information on who corrected your question will be found there too.<br />\r\nThe upper one tells you who edited the question and when this was done. Similar information can be found next to the texts etc.</div>', '', 0, 1, '2006-03-11 19:10:58: Marc-Oliver Pahl'),
(9, 'Suggestions/ complaints explanation', '[HTML]\r\n<!-- This element is used for the collection with the suggest/ complain input -->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nYou will find this page on each prelab and also at the end of each lab.<br>\r\nWe always try to improve the lab and who could make better suggestions than you, the participants?<br>\r\nSo if you have any problems or improvement suggestions concerning the (pre-)lab, please provide them to us!<br>\r\nThis input will also be present for your lab session and is <b>not relevant for your prelab finishing</b>...\r\n</p>', '', 0, 1, '2007-09-04 18:03:56: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2006-03-11 19:10:58: Marc-Oliver Pahl'),
(10, 'Willkommen auf der Seite des eLearning-Systems Labsystem!', '[HTML]\r\n<!-- click on the icon with the eye (second one) on the upper right to see how this page looks like! -->\r\n\r\n<h3>__ELEMENTTITLE__</h3>\r\n\r\n<div style="disply: inline; float: right; width: 40px; height: 15px; text-align: right;">\r\n<a href="../pages/view.php?address=p3&__LINKQUERY__&lng=en"><img src="../pix/en.gif" width="25" height="15" style="border: none;" alt="in English"></a>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h4>Was ist das Labsystem?</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n  Das Labsystem ist eine <b>webbasierte</b> eLearning-Plattform.<br />\r\n  Das Labsystem unterst&uuml;tzt Sie beim Erstellen Ihrer Kurse, bei deren Durchf&uuml;hrung und bei ihrer Verwaltung!\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div style="text-align: center;">\r\n <img src="../pix/startpage.jpg" width="400" height="144" style="border: 0;" alt="A street in Bordeaux, France; &copy; Marc-Oliver Pahl, Summer 2005" />\r\n <div style="padding-left: 0.5em; padding-right: 0.5em; text-align: center; font-size: 0.7em;">A street in Bordeaux, France; &copy; Marc-Oliver Pahl, Summer 2005</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2 style="font-size: 1.5em; color:#888888;">\r\n  Probieren Sie das Labsystem hier aus!\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Als <a href="http://demo.labsystem.m-o-p.de/?userrole=user"><strong>Teilnehmer</strong></a> (So sehen Kursteilnehmer das System!)</li>\r\n  <li>Als <a href="http://demo.labsystem.m-o-p.de/?userrole=corrector"><strong>Korrektor</strong></a>  (So sieht das System f&uuml;r Korrektoren aus!)</li>\r\n  <li>Als <a href="http://demo.labsystem.m-o-p.de/?userrole=all"><strong>Vollzugreifer</strong></a> (In dieser Rolle sind Sie f&uuml;r fast die gesamte Funktionalit&auml;t freigeschaltet! Als Editor, Scheduler, Korrektor, ...)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 0.7em; color: #888888">(It takes 5 seconds to restore the database.)</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="font-size: 1.3em; color:#888888;">\r\n  Was sind die Vorteile gerade dieses Systems?\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Es ist komplett webbasert...\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>...Sie ben&ouml;tigen daher lediglich einen Webbrowser, um mit dem System zu arbeiten. Im Bereich der Lehre wird diese Voraussetzung zusammen mit einem Internetanschluss fast jeder Rechner erf&uuml;llen. Wenn Sie es online stellen ist es von jedem Rechner im Internet zu erreichen.</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n  <li>Es ist sehr einfach und schnell konfigurierbar...\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>...daher k&ouml;nnen Sie nach dem Entpacken des Archives sofort anfangen. Neue Kursse sind mit wenigen Anpassungen an einer kopierten ini-Datei eingerichtet!</li>\r\n    <li>...und optimal auf die Bed&uuml;rfnisse von Autoren, Studierenden, Korrektoren und Kursleitern abgestimmt, da es genau in diesem Umfeld entwickelt wurde.</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n  <li>Es ist extrem schnell...\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>...da die Umgebung ohne gro&szlig;e Grafiken auskommt und daher die Seiten nur wenig Bandbreite brauchen.</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n  <li>Es ist erprobt...\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>...da wir es in der <a href="http://www.informatik.uni-tuebingen.de" target="_blank">Informatik</a> an der <a href="http://www.uni-tuebingen.de" target="_blank">Universit&auml;t T&uuml;bingen</a> seit Jahren erfolgreich einsetzen.</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n  <li>Das System bietet...\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>selbstkorrigierende Multiple-Choice-Fragen</li>\r\n <li>Freitexteingaben</li>\r\n <li>Authoring-Funktionalit&auml;t</li>\r\n <li>Korrekturfunktionalit&auml;t</li>\r\n <li>Course Management</li>\r\n <li>breite Konfigurierbarkeit</li>\r\n <li><strong>Mehrsprachenunterst&uuml;tzung</strong>, die alle Ausgaben, Kn&ouml;pfe etc. des Systems in der gew&uuml;nschten Sprache erscheinen l&auml;sst (Lediglich eine Datei muss dazu in die gew&uuml;nschte Sprache &uuml;bersetzt werden.)</li>\r\n <li>eine einfache Schnittstelle zu existierenden Autentisierungsverfahren an Ihrer Universit&auml;t, Schule, Ihrem Unternehmen,  ...</li>\r\n <li><strong>schnelle funktionale Erweiterbarkeit</strong> (Die Lernobjekte z.B. sind php-Klassen zu denen man leicht neue hinzuf&uuml;gen kann.)</li>\r\n <li><strong>WYSIWYG</strong> durch die Einbindung von tinyMCE</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n  <li>\r\n    Grunds&auml;tzliche &Uuml;berlegungen, ob es sinnvoll ist, einen Kurs auf Basis einer eLearning-Plattform durchzuf&uuml;hren finden sich <a href="http://www.m-o-p.de/life/src2/2007-07-27_studienarbeit_pahl_eLearning.pdf">hier</a>.\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n  <li>\r\n    Ein Vortrag &uuml;ber den Einsatz an der Uni-T&uuml;bingen, der erl&auml;utert, welche Vorteile der Einsatz bei uns bringt, findet sich <a href="http://www.m-o-p.de/life/src2/2007-07-30_Vortrag_eLearning.ram">hier</a>.\r\n  </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="font-size: 1.3em; color:#888888;">\r\n  Wo kann ich das System bekommen?\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Hier!\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Sie k&ouml;nnen die <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p13&__LINKQUERY__">zip-Datei mit dem PHP-Source-Code hier L A D E N.</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Sie m&uuml;ssen die Datei nur auf Ihren Webserver entpacken und das setup-Script aufrufen.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="font-size: 0.8em">\r\n  Die Datei enth&auml;lt das vollst&auml;ndige System. Sie k&ouml;nnen es also ausgiebig testen.<br />\r\n  Die Weitergabe jeglicher Teile des Systems ohne schriftliche Genehmigung des Autors ist untersagt.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3 style="font-size: 1.3em; color:#888888;">\r\n  Wie kann ich das System erwerben?\r\n</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n  Das System wird bald als OpenSource-Projekt auf Sourceforge stehen. Bitte gedulden Sie sich bis Anfang 2010. Danke!\r\n</p>', '', 0, 0, '2009-12-11 22:45:44: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2007-12-29 17:13:57: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2007-12-29 17:12:11: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2007-09-17 16:00:39: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2007-09-05 19:44:46: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2007-09-05 19:20:32: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2007-09-05 19:18:10: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2006-05-06 01:09:56: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2006-03-24 20:10:06: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2006-03-11 20:02:18: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2006-03-11 19:47:00: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2006-03-11 19:45:55: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2006-03-11 19:44:23: Marc-Oliver Pahl\n2006-03-11 19:37:50: Marc-Oliver Pahl: - created -'),
(11, 'FAQ', '[HTML]\r\n<!-- click on the icon with the eye (second one) on the upper right to see how this page looks like! -->\r\n\r\n<h3>__ELEMENTTITLE__</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>What about the Lock?</b><br />\r\n<p>\r\nThe inputs are arbitrated by a lock. \r\nEach Team can only open one input at the same time.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThis serves two purposes:\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>It prevents the team partners to work non cooperatively by answering the questions not together\r\n  <li>It helps significantly not to forget saving an answer (as there is no Ajax this is not done automatically!)\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHow does the lock work now?\r\nSuppose we have computer A and B. \r\nBoth load the same question sheet so both see the ìgive answer&Ouml;î buttons.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSuppose A opens a question.\r\nThe lock is set to that question now.\r\nAs A and B are working independently, B wants to open another question.\r\nB clicks on ìgive answer&Ouml;î of a question.\r\nThe system notices that B clicked on the button that was only visible since the view of A and B was inconsistent and just reloads the page on B.\r\nB sees now red locks (as A) on all non open questions and the question A opened is open at B now too.\r\nOf course B only sees the last saved answer of the question A answered so there might be no answer visible even though A wrote already something (but did not save).\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIf someone clicks on a red lock below a question, the system assumes, the person understands that it grabs the lock from another input by this and forces a lock take.\r\n(This might be useful if one does not know anymore, which question one opened.)\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSuppose now the case B grabbed the lock but A does not know that (they should cooperate so this should NEVER happen).\r\nA wants to save the answer but the lock is not set to the question anymore.\r\nInstead of discarding the answer what would be the normal case as the team did not coordinate itself, the system saves the answer now anyway but replaces all spaces by ìNO_LOCKî to show the team that this behavior was not intended.\r\n</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n <li><b>On newly saved pages slashes (&#92;) do appear in the source code!</b>\r\n<p>\r\n     A reason for that might be the magic quote feature of php (escaped characters get reescaped).<br />\r\n     Solution: Edit the include/classes/DBConnection.inc. Bottom!\r\n</p>\r\n  </li>\r\n\r\n</ul>', '', 1, 0, '2006-03-11 20:47:22: Marc-Oliver Pahl: - created -'),
(12, 'Finish Prelab', '[HTML]\r\n<!-- This element is used for the collection with the suggest/ complain input -->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nGot to the Menu Entry "<a href=''../pages/view.php?address=l2.allPrelabQ&__LINKQUERY__''>all questions</a>" to finish the Prelab!\r\n</p>', '', 0, 1, '2007-09-04 18:05:40: Marc-Oliver Pahl: - created -'),
(13, 'Username/ Password reminder from __SYSTEMTITLE__', 'Hello __FORENAME__ __NAME__ (__USERNAME__),\r\n\r\nsomeone requested a new password for you account at __SYSTEMTITLE__.\r\nFrom now on you can only logon with the new password printed at the bottom of this email.\r\n\r\nYou can change the password as well as your username on the user administration website.\r\n\r\nEnjoy the lab!\r\n\r\n--\r\n\r\nHere is your new log on information:\r\n', '', 1024, 0, '2012-01-23 02:16:48: Marc-Oliver Pahl - created -\n'),
(14, 'Registration page', '[HTML]\n<h1 style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.5em;">\n  <a href="http://labsystem.sf.net/">labsystem</a> (6 SWS/ 10 ECTS)\n</h1>\n\n<div style="text-align: center">\n</div>\n\n<h3>\n  What is the intended audience?\n</h3>\n\n<p>\n  The intended audience of this course is <b>master</b> students with deeper interest and\n  background in computer networks.<br>\n  Basic knowledge in networking is required on a theoretical (e.g. lecture "Grundlagen:\n  Rechnernetze und Verteilte Systeme") and a practical level (e.g. <a href=\n  "http://ilab.net.in.tum.de/">ilab</a> or own practical experience).\n</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>You should be familiar with the <b>Linux</b> Operating system at Shell level.\n  </li>\n\n  <li>You should beable to <b>write programs</b> in at least one programming language (e.g. Java,\n  C, python).\n  </li>\n\n  <li>You should either have attended our <a href="http://ilab.net.in.tum.de/">bachelor practical\n  exercise ilab</a> or be familiar with the <a href=\n  "http://ilab.net.in.tum.de?address=accessableLabs">topics it covers</a>.\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>\n  If you already know how the Internet works and you want to learn about selected networking\n  concepts more in depth ilab<sup>2</sup> is the right course for you.<br>\n  If you are not familiar with configuring services like DNS, VPN, Firewalls etc. <a href=\n  "http://ilab.net.in.tum.de?address=register">iLab1</a> is the right course for you.\n</p>\n\n<h3>\n  What do I learn?\n</h3>\n\n<p>\n  When finishing the course, you will have a <b>deep inside</b> into the covered topics. You can\n  find a list of the topics <a href="http://ilab2.net.in.tum.de?address=accessableLabs">here</a>.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  You will get a good overview in the topics handled at our chair and therefore be <b>well prepared\n  to do a thesis or a student assistant</b> work at our chair later.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  As the <b>entire course</b> is held in <b>English</b> you can train and improve your language\n  skills.\n</p>\n\n<h3>\n  How is the workflow?\n</h3>\n\n<p>\n  The course consists of ten exercises.<br>\n  For an exercise you will normally have one week; for longer exercises two weeks will be\n  scheduled.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  The practical exercises are performed in <b>teams of two students</b>.<br>\n  You should try to find a team partner that is on a similar level concerning the knowledge about\n  the network backgrounds, as well as the Linux operating system.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  An exercise consists of three parts:\n</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>A short weekly meeting where you get presented some theoretical background for the upcoming\n  exercise.\n  </li>\n\n  <li>A so-called "prelab" where you make yourself familiar with the theoretical backgrounds of the\n  current exercise.<br>\n    This is done by each team member separately on ones own.<br>\n    The prelab is done before the practical performance of the exercise.\n  </li>\n\n  <li>The practical exercise which is called "lab".<br>\n    As stated above this part is done in your two-people team.<br>\n    You will have your lab environment for one whole day of the week on which you can decide freely\n    when to be in the lab and perform your practical exercise together.<br>\n    This gives you the freedom to attend lectures in between, etc.\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>\n  The course is entirely held in <b>English</b>.<br>\n  You are expected to answer the questions in English as well.<br>\n  This is a good example to exercise and improve your language skills!\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  In contrast to many other practical exercises the course is entirely based on a <b><a href=\n  "http://labsystem.sourceforge.net/">web system</a></b>.<br>\n  You will have access to the respective website from every PC that is connected to the\n  Internet.<br>\n  This allows you to freely choose your timeslots to perform the prelab or do final adjustments to\n  the answers.\n</p>\n\n<h3>\n  To which modules does this course belong?\n</h3>\n\n<p style="margin-bottom: 1em">\n</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>IN8903: Praktikum im Bereich Technische Informatik (10 ECTS)\n  </li>\n\n  <li>IN2106: Master-Praktikum (10 ECTS)\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>\n  When does the course start?\n</h3>\n\n<p>\n  The kickoff will usually be in the first week of the semester. Please have a look at our <a href=\n  "http://www.net.in.tum.de/">chairs page</a> for further information.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  In the kickoff the teams will be formed and the timeslots will be allocated thus you have to\n  physically attend this meeting.\n</p>\n\n<h3>\n  How can I apply?\n</h3>\n\n<p>\n  You find the registration form below\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  As the practical exercises are performed in teams of two students, it is a good idea to already\n  search a team partner right now.<br>\n  You can give the name of your designated team partner in the application form.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  As the places are usually in great demand you should register early.\n</p>\n\n<h3>\n  Current State of Applications\n</h3>\n\n<p>\n  The amount of free places is shown below the form.<br>\n  Please <b>continue registering even if no places are left as usually not all students really\n  participate at the end</b>.<br>\n  The final decision about this will be at the kickoff.\n</p>', '', 1024, 0, '2012-01-23 01:20:19: Marc-Oliver Pahl - created -\n'),
(15, 'Thank you for registering!', '[HTML]\n<h1 style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.5em;">\n  <a href="http://ilab2.net.in.tum.de/">iLab2</a> (6 SWS/ 10 ECTS)\n</h1>\n\n<div style="text-align: center">\n</div>\n\n<h3>\n  Thank you for registering to iLab2!\n</h3>\n\n<p>\n  The system has sent you further instructions via email.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  Having your login information you can directly start\n</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>making yourself familiar with the system\n  </li>\n\n  <li>change your user name and your password\n  </li>\n\n  <li>getting an insight to the laboratory rooms infrastructure\n  </li>\n\n  <li>having an overlook over the basics for the programming languages used\n  </li>\n\n  <li>and much more...\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>\n  Further information and the link are in the email you received.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  The <b>next mandatory event for you is being present at the kickoff meeting - usually in the\n  first week of the next semester</b>.\n</p>', '', 0, 0, '2012-01-23 01:21:24: Marc-Oliver Pahl - created -\n'),
(16, 'Thank you for registering to __SYSTEMTITLE__', 'Welcome to the iLab2!\r\n\r\nYou have successfully registered to the course. \r\n\r\nIf you already had an account in the labsystem it is still valid.\r\nIf you are a new participant you will receive your logon data from\r\nthe system already today.\r\n\r\nOne speciality of the ilab is that it is entirely supported by a\r\nspecial web system. If you want you can directly start making\r\nyourself familiar with the system. To do so simply logon to this\r\npage:\r\n       http://ilab2.net.in.tum.de?config=useradmin\r\n\r\nYou can also change your user name and your password on this\r\npage. So it is a good idea to log on ;)\r\n\r\nThe system also provides you already with an insight to the\r\nlaboratory room''s infrastructure and basics for the program-\r\nming languages used.\r\n\r\nYou find everything in the menu after logging in.\r\n\r\nThe next mandatory event for the practical exercise is the\r\nkickoff meeting in the *first week of the semester*.\r\n\r\nThere the teams of two people each will be built and the\r\ntimeslots in the laboratory room will be assigned to the\r\nteams.\r\nIf you are not sure with whom you want to do the lab\r\nmaybe it is a good chance to ask some of your friends if\r\nthey also want to participate. Of course you can also find\r\na team partner at the kickoff.\r\n\r\nWe wish you already a lot of fun with the exercises!\r\n\r\nBest regards, Marc-Oliver Pahl\r\n\r\nYour iLab2 advisors are:\r\nXYZ\r\nMarc-Oliver Pahl <pahl@net.in.tum.de>\r\nIf you have anz questions they are happy to help you.', '', 1024, 0, '2012-01-23 01:22:34: Marc-Oliver Pahl - created -\n'),
(17, 'edit system mails and info', '[HTML]\n<h3>\n  __ELEMENTTITLE__\n</h3>\n\n<p>\n  On this page you can edit the emails, the system sends and the information shown on the\n  registration page.\n</p>\n\n<p>\n  The elements linked here are only the default elements. Please refer to the config constants for\n  information about which pages are used in your instance:\n</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>/php/uaUnPwRemind.php (&lt;- PidPasswordMail)\n  </li>\n\n  <li>/pages/register.php (&amp;lt- PidRegistrationPage, PidAfterRegistrationPage,\n  PidRegistrationMail)\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>\n  If you did not change the default you can edit as follows:\n</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p13&amp;__LINKQUERY__">Password reminder email</a>\n  </li>\n\n  <li>\n    <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p14&amp;__LINKQUERY__">Registration page text</a>\n  </li>\n\n  <li>\n    <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p15&amp;__LINKQUERY__">After registration thank you text</a>\n  </li>\n\n  <li>\n    <a href="../pages/view.php?address=p16&amp;__LINKQUERY__">Registration email</a>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p class="note">\n  For emails the title of the page will become the subject line. You can use all page constants in\n  your mail.\n</p>\n\n<p class="note">\n  This page is editable as well of course... Click on the pen on the top right.\n</p>', '', 1024, 0, '2012-01-23 03:20:38: Marc-Oliver Pahl - created -\n');

